HEADWORD: Camembert cheese
<hw>Camembert cheese</hw></mhw>. <def>A kind of rich, soft, unpressed
cream cheese made in the vicinity of Camembert, near Argentan, France;
also, any cheese of the same type, wherever made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

